This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) as it proposes a novel approach for unsupervised paraphrase generation. The paper also involves optimization techniques and language fluency, which are common topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper deals with semantic similarity and information retrieval (cs.IR) and involves local editing, which is a common technique in neural networks (cs.NE).
